  "body": "I recently stumbled upon `SimulatedBackend` struct while browsing the code. I noticed that it has a constructor (i.e. `NewSimulatedBackendWithDatabase`) which apparently accepts the path to the node's LevelDB, which is `geth/chaindata` (right?).\r\n\r\nNow, since `SimulatedBackend` provides several functions like `CallContract`, `SendTransaction` etc., my guess is that its purpose is to simulate the outcomes of mock transactions, or even contract calls. However, when specifying the path to a runnning node's chaindata, the client failed to start with `resource temporarily unavailable` error. Stopping the node just for this purpose doesn't seem to be a grand idea.\r\n\r\nDoes anyone have experience with this `SimulatedBackend`? If so, what's the best approach to get it up and running?\r\n\r\nThanks",
